<DOC><DOCNO> AP881202-0093 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-02-88 1347EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Britain-Explosion     12-02 0147</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Britain-Explosion,0151</SECOND><HEAD>Explosion Shatters Windows at Atomic Weapons Center</HEAD><DATELINE>BURGHFIELD, England (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A controlled explosion at a governmentatomic weapons factory shattered windows Friday, but there were noinjuries, the Ministry of Defense said.   The blast at the Atomic Weapons Establishment in an area setaside for destroying conventional explosives occurred with moreforce than expected, a defense spokeswoman saidy.   Martin O'Neill, the opposition Labor Party spokesman on defensematters, called for an inquiry at the site, 40 miles southwest ofLondon.   ``The veil of secrecy which surrounds activities atestablishments like Burghfield has to be lifted when the public andthe surrounding area have been disturbed and shocked by an explosionsuch as this,'' he said.   Bruce Kent of the Campaign for Nuclear Disarmament said ``it isincredible that conventional explosives should be destroyed byburning in the middle of a nuclear bomb factory.''</TEXT></DOC>